      "id": "eagle-6",
      "title": "Eagle 6",
      "description": "Eagle 6 is a cybersecurity product that secures large enterprises by detecting unknown vulnerabilities before they expose systems to risk. My primary role included the implementation of the frontend portion of different features and modules of the product using Angular and a host of other related premium and open source libraries in an Agile-driven environment.\n\n- Implemented Frontend for Cloud Storage and Organization Chart Modeling Modules of the flagship enterprise product of the company alongside the integration of various rich text document editing tools and their customization via angular-ized plugins.\n- Implemented frontend for file and folder management including role-based permissions assignment for each file/folder, ability to preview and edit contents of each file/folder based on the type of file, and user's permission.\n- Implemented complex plugin-based online editors for opening both short and full-featured documents with the ability to view/edit Microsoft Office files and support for comments, concurrent editing, permission-based content viewing/editing, and pdf export.\n- Implemented frontend for chunked file and folder upload using TUS protocol for scalability and support for uploading large files.\n- Implemented a new iteration of the Organization Chart Modeling tool in GOJS architecting the data access and state management of this module using Akita (Redux, Flux based State Management Library) for scalability and robust maintenance.\n- Implemented and Maintained different types of graphs and maps of Network Monitoring tools module using d3, Highcharts, leaflet, and OSM Tiles server.\n- Implemented different components of the app from concept through deployment.\n- Interviewed and facilitated the hiring of multiple Frontend developers for the team I was assigned to.\n- Facilitated in driving code quality and scalability by restructuring and implementing Redux, Flux based data flow & state management for different modules & components alongside reviewing, providing feedback to fellow UI developers on their code contributions.\n- Standardized all output with a new responsive & accessible UI using Google material design standards.\n- Assessed UX and UI designs for technical feasibility and provided estimates for their implementation.\n- Collaborated with product team members to implement new feature developments.\n- Worked in an Agile-driven environment to effectively maintain project timelines and utilize available resources.\n- Stack used: Angular 2+, Angular Material, TUS, RxJS, Akita (Redux, Flux based State Management library), GoJS, D3, Highcharts, leaflet, OSM, Typescript, BEM, Jest & SCSS.",
